{"TopicId":212940,"ForumId":196,"TopicTitle":"Can\u0027t exit EAS-1 Grumble seat command chair","CreatedByName":"Kaa253","CreatedById":68628,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T04:08:25Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kaa253","CreatedById":68628,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T04:08:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs the title says. Kerbals can\u0027t leave the command seat and they can\u0027t go on EVA from the seat.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAttempts at EVA say \u0022EVA is disabled due to an obstacle.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shzt93","CreatedById":203349,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T08:12:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsay \u0022EVA is disabled due to an obstacle.\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u00221-A90-DOVFQ9-XRIF-3-V2-DZDB.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022180\u0022 width=\u0022180\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/HgDFRnL/1-A90-DOVFQ9-XRIF-3-V2-DZDB.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022M4-OMTS31-T-0-YO6-SC6-CQ-6.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022180\u0022 title=\u0022\u0022 width=\u0022180\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/Hxs4DJv/M4-OMTS31-T-0-YO6-SC6-CQ-6.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022I1-TX4-BC-UH4-C-BJS-O5-2.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022180\u0022 title=\u0022\u0022 width=\u0022180\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/ggQVrG0/I1-TX4-BC-UH4-C-BJS-O5-2.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00224-ILLOMDJ-V7-RC-4-JI7-MP3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022100.00\u0022 height=\u0022180\u0022 width=\u0022180\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/rxPh4zc/4-ILLOMDJ-V7-RC-4-JI7-MP3.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T08:28:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203349-shzt93/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022203349\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203349-shzt93/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@shzt93\u003C/a\u003E, this looks like a bug so thread moved from KSP 2 Tech support to KSP 2 Bug reports. I just tested this and it seems that EVA is blocked if the seat is\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003Eorientated in this way:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XWI4UCi.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002288.92\u0022 height=\u0022668\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XWI4UCi.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Whippler","CreatedById":143730,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T08:32:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have same problem when its mounted on a panel. But if its at the front edge of the panel, you can actually EVA from it. I think the eva spot that it checks is a little too low in the front of the seat and gets obstructed by the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002295.82\u0022 height=\u0022687\u0022 width=\u0022717\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1079312881826418688/1079312882052907049/image.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-26T10:12:36Z\u0022 title=\u002202/26/2023 10:12  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 26, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Whippler\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kaa253","CreatedById":68628,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T10:01:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease move this post to Bug reports\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AngryKerbs","CreatedById":226340,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T13:49:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame bug here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T13:52:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThread moved to KSP 2 Bug Reports and overlapping thread merged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serialboxes","CreatedById":226671,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T19:45:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think I figured it out, the collision check is below the chair, if you gizmo the chair up at least this high EVA becomes available\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png?width=1582\u0026amp;height=890\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002274.17\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1079484000629956800/1079489088631083188/image.png?width=1582\u0026amp;height=890\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png?width=1582\u0026amp;height=890\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002274.17\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1079484000629956800/1079489141462532237/image.png?width=1582\u0026amp;height=890\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}